<br>
The Polished Granite Tomahawk from reports creates an item called Abjuration Binding. The spell effect on the weapon however is Berserker Strength which is a low level enc spell, which is Alteration based.<br>
<br>
Screaming Mace then creates something total different, a Spell: Screaming Mace.<br>
<br>
I heard the SoY is a valid item also, but have not seen which item is produced when you combine it in the sages box.<br>
<br>
One would think that creating &quot;bindings&quot; for each magic circle (abj, alt, div, ...) would be the way to go, since this would give five different bindings and support our theory that each sage quest yields five results that need to be combined finally, somehow. It may be worth to look specifically for items which have an effect with a certain magic skill, and try them in the box.<br>
<br>
I also thought of some final way to combine the results then...do you remember the parchments used in practice research? (not ethereal or spectral parchments <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Maybe you need to put one into the box or grimoire along with the results of the three quests to create something, after all a spell needs place to be scribed on...<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
